//sights list strings 1st sight Nyhavn Especially during summer Nyhavn is the perfect place to end a long day. Have dinner at one of the cosy restaurants or do like the locals and buy a beer from a nearby store and enjoy the view. Daily between 10 until 22, and even later in the summertime weekends. Nyhavn 1 to 71, 1051 København K www.nyhavn.com +45 33 12 32 33
//sights list strings 2nd sight Tivoli Gardens Tivoli Gardens amusement park in Copenhagen is a must for all visitors to the city, young and old. Daily between 10 until 23 Vesterbrogade 3, 1630 København V www.tivoligardens.com +45 33 15 10 01
//sights list strings 3rd sight Little Mermaid At Langelinje Pier you will find one of Copenhagen\'s most famous tourist attractions: The sculpture of The Little Mermaid. Daily between 10, until sunset. RLangelinie, 2100 København Ø www.mermaidsculpture.dk +45 24 27 96 02 (contact if you want to buy one)
//sights list strings 4th sight Christiania Ready for something different? Then head out to freetown Christiania in the district of Christianshavn. Daily between 10 until 22, and even later in the summertime. Prinsessegade, 1422 København K nytforum@christiania.org +45 3295 6507
//sights list strings 5th sight Strøget The largest shopping area is centered around Strøget in the heart of the city. Strøget is one of Europe\'\s longest pedestrian streets with a wealth of shops. All days between 10 and 19, and 23 for restaurants Frederiksberggade, 1459 København K www.kcc.dk No contact for this location.
//castels list strings -1st castel Christiansborg Palace Christiansborg Palace, located on the tiny island of Slotsholmen, contains the Danish Parliament Folketinget, the Supreme Court, and the Ministry of State. Monday-Sunday from 10 to 17. Prins Jørgens Gård, 1468 København K www.kongeligeslotte.dk +45 33 92 64 92
//castels list strings -2nd castel Kronborg Castle Kronborg Castle is probably the most famous Danish castle, known worldwide from Shakespeare\'s Hamlet. Tuesday to Sunday, from 11 to 17. Kronborg 2C, 3000 Helsingør www.kongeligeslotte.dk +45 49 21 30 78
//castels list strings -3rd castel Amalienborg Palace Amalienborg Palace is a must for anyone with a taste for royal history and the life of Denmark’s royal family who still resides inside the palace. Monday to Sunday from 10 to 17. Amalienborg, 1257 København K www.kongernessamling.dk +45 33 12 21 86
//castels list strings 4th castel Rosenborg Castle A royal hermitage set in the King’s Garden in the heart of Copenhagen, Rosenborg Castle features 400 years of splendor, royal art treasures and the Crown Jewels and Royal Regalia. Monday to Sunday from 10 to 17. Øster Voldgade 4A, 1350 København K www.kongernessamling.dk/rosenborg +45 33 15 32 86
//castels list strings -5th castel Frederiksborg Castle Frederiksborg Palace is situated on three islets in the castle lake in Hillerød, north of Copenhagen. Monday to Sunday from 10 to 17. Møntportvejen 10, 3400 Hillerød www.frederiksborgslot.dk +45 48 26 04 39
//bars list strings -1st bar Jazzhus Montmartre Legendary venue for live jazz with a program of gigs by famous American and European musicians. In the weekends between 17.30 to 02, and 24 Tuesday/Thursday. Store Regnegade 19A, 1110 København K montmartre@bojesen.dk +45 27 90 30 63
//bars list strings 2nd bar Blume High level innovative cocktails and extraordinary service, combined with intimate sorroundings and a distinct music profile will ensure the remarkable party. Friday til Sunday, from 20 until 5. Studiestræde 14,1455 Købehavn Ks wwww.blumecph.dk +45 60 61 71 58
//bars list strings 3rd bar Bar7 Stylish bar for drinks and cocktails in a choice of rooms with comfy designer sofas and funky decor. All days between 16 and 4. Closed on Monday. Studiestræde 7, 1455 København K www.bar7.dk +45 27 77 77 87
//sights list strings 4th bar Ruby Classic and creative modern cocktails in a cool hangout with comfy sofas and an intimate ambience. Every day, from 16 until 2. Nybrogade 10, 1203 København K www.rby.dk +45 33 93 12 03
//sights list strings 5th bar Mexibar The bar has existed for many years and is known for its festive atmosphere and cheap cocktails. Monday to Saturday , from 19 until 3. Elmegade 27, 2200 København N www.mexibar.com +45 35 37 77 66
//restaurants list - 1st restaurant Cock\'s and cows At Cock\'s and Cows there is a burger for everyone. There is everything from the traditional cheeseburger to a big burger with pork called The Bohemian Pork Rib. Everyday between 11 until 22. Longer hours during weekends. Gammel Strand 34, 1202 København K www.cocksandcows.dk +45 69 69 60 00
//restaurant list strings 2nd restaurant The Union Kitchen The Union Kitchen is located in Store Strandstræde street near Nyhavn in Copenhagen. Here you will be served breakfast, English \"balls\" and tasteful cocktails in classic surroundings. All days from 8 until 17, and midnight in weekends. Store Strandstrade 21, 1255 København K www.theunionkitchen.dk +45 33 14 54 88
//restaurant list strings 3rd restaurant Nova Located in central Copenhagen just off Stroget, Nova is an ideal place for a break on a shoppedag or for a cozy dinner with friends and family. Everyday from 11 until midnight. Skindergade 34, 1159 København K www.restaurantnova.com +45 33 11 12 49
//restaurant list strings 4th restaurant Nimb Bar\'n\'Grill Nimb Bar\'n\'Grill Tivoli serves seafood and steakhouse classics with a creative culinary edge.In the middle of Tivoli Gardens you will find Nimb Bar\'n\'Grill, which, as the name reveals, offers both great steaks as well as alcohol. Monday to Saturday, from 17 to 23. Bernstorffsgade 5,1577 København V www.bargrill.nimb.dk +45 88 70 00 60
//restaurant list strings 5th restaurant Restaurant Kanalen Beautiful, idyllic and with the serenity of old Copenhagen lies Restaurant Kanalen in the house that used to serve as customs office for the area of Christianshavn. Monday to Saturday, from 11.30 to 23.30. Wilders Plads 2, 1403 København K www.restaurant-kanalen.dk +45 32 95 13 30
